corecluster (16.03.11) stable; urgency=low

  * Created new universal render function
  * Moved get and get_list to algorithms directory
  * Fixed new hook mechanism
  * Updated license headers
  * Moved system.call to corenetwork package
  * Added support for network namespaces to isolated networks
  * Python egg is packed into debian package
  * Vnc address is assigned to VM, not to CoreCluster. This will be used in multi-agent env.
  * Changed behavior of agents vm, image and network: if related object is nor ready, task fails
  * Fixed storage mount error
  * Task graph in administrator's panel
  * Agent stops when is in stopping or done state
  * vm check action for cli to restore vm from failed state (if present in libvirt)
  * Websocket vnc is supported

 -- Marta Nabozny <martastrzet@gmail.com> 10 Mar 2016 10:00:00 +0200


